headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Cummins (CMI) After A 49% One-Year Rally?
summary: Wondering if Cummins at its current price still offers value, or if the best days are already reflected in the share price? This article is designed to help you frame that question clearly. After reaching a last close of US$540.65, the stock has recently seen a 7.4% decline over the past week and a 1.1% decline over the past month, while still showing a 3.6% return year to date and a 49.4% return over the past year, plus a 135.9% return over three years and 151.0% over five years. headline: CMI Q4 Deep Dive: Power Systems Strength Balances Truck Market Weakness, Tariffs Pressure Margins
summary: Engine manufacturer Cummins (NYSE:CMI) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 1.1% year on year to $8.54 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $5.81 per share was 14.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Cummins (CMI) Is Down 7.4% After Issuing 2026 Revenue and Margin Guidance - What's Changed
summary: Cummins Inc. recently reported fourth-quarter 2025 results showing sales of US$8,536 million and net income of US$593 million, alongside full-year 2025 sales of US$33.67 billion and earnings per share of about US$20.50 from continuing operations.
